 <sect1 id="release-8-3-23">
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
  <title>Release 8.3.23</title>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
  <title>版本8.3.23</title>

  <formalpara>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
  <title>Release date:</title>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
  <title>发布日期：</title>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
  <para>2013-02-07</para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
  <para>2013-02-07</para> 
  </formalpara>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
   This release contains a variety of fixes from 8.3.22.
   For information about new features in the 8.3 major release, see
   <xref linkend="release-8-3">.
  </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
   该发布包含来自8.3.22中各种修复。关于8.3主要发布中新特性信息，
   参阅<xref linkend="release-8-3">。
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
   This is expected to be the last <productname>PostgreSQL</> release
   in the 8.3.X series.  Users are encouraged to update to a newer
   release branch soon.
  </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
    预计这是8.3.X系列中最后<productname>PostgreSQL</>发布。
鼓励用户尽快更新到新版本分支。
</para>

  <sect2>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
   <title>Migration to Version 8.3.23</title>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
   <title>迁移到版本8.3.23</title>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
    A dump/restore is not required for those running 8.3.X.
   </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
   运行8.3.X不需要备份/恢复。
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
    However, if you are upgrading from a version earlier than 8.3.17,
    see <xref linkend="release-8-3-17">.
   </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
   然而，如果从8.3.17更早版本更新，参阅8.3.17发布说明。
</para>

  </sect2>

  <sect2>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
  <title>Changes</title>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
  <title>变化</title>

   <itemizedlist>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Prevent execution of <function>enum_recv</> from SQL (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
   避免来自SQL <function>enum_recv</>的执行(Tom Lane)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      The function was misdeclared, allowing a simple SQL command to crash the
      server.  In principle an attacker might be able to use it to examine the
      contents of server memory.  Our thanks to Sumit Soni (via Secunia SVCRP)
      for reporting this issue.  (CVE-2013-0255)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
    该函数被错误声明，使得简单SQL命令造成服务器崩溃。
原则上攻击者可能使用它检查服务器内存的内容。
非常感谢Sumit Soni(通过Secunia SVCRP)报告这个问题(CVE-2013-0255) 
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix SQL grammar to allow subscripting or field selection from a
      sub-SELECT result (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
    修复SQL语法以允许来自子SELECT结果的下标或者字段选择(Tom Lane)
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Protect against race conditions when scanning
      <structname>pg_tablespace</> (Stephen Frost, Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
    当扫描<structname>pg_tablespace</>的时候，防止竞态条件(Stephen Frost, Tom Lane)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      <command>CREATE DATABASE</> and <command>DROP DATABASE</> could
      misbehave if there were concurrent updates of
      <structname>pg_tablespace</> entries.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
   如果有<structname>pg_tablespace</>项的并发更新，
   那么<command>CREATE DATABASE</>和<command>DROP DATABASE</>可能误操作。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Prevent <command>DROP OWNED</> from trying to drop whole databases or
      tablespaces (&Aacute;lvaro Herrera)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
    防止<command>DROP OWNED</>尝试删除整个数据库或者表空间(&Aacute;lvaro Herrera) 
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      For safety, ownership of these objects must be reassigned, not dropped.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para> 
    出于安全考虑，这些对象的所有权被重新分配，而不是被删除。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Prevent misbehavior when a <symbol>RowExpr</> or <symbol>XmlExpr</>
      is parse-analyzed twice (Andres Freund, Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
    当<symbol>RowExpr</>或者<symbol>XmlExpr</>被解析分析两次的时候，
避免误操作(Andres Freund, Tom Lane)  
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      This mistake could be user-visible in contexts such as
      <literal>CREATE TABLE LIKE INCLUDING INDEXES</>.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
   该错误在上下文中是用户可见的，比如<literal>CREATE TABLE LIKE INCLUDING INDEXES</>。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Improve defenses against integer overflow in hashtable sizing
      calculations (Jeff Davis)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
   提高在哈希大小计算中防御整数溢出(Jeff Davis)
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Ensure that non-ASCII prompt strings are translated to the correct
      code page on Windows (Alexander Law, Noah Misch)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
    确保非ASCII提示字符串被转换为Windows上正确代码页(Alexander Law, Noah Misch)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      This bug affected <application>psql</> and some other client programs.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
   这个错误影响<application>psql</>以及一些其他的客户端程序。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix possible crash in <application>psql</>'s <command>\?</> command
      when not connected to a database (Meng Qingzhong)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
    当不连接到数据库的时候，修复<application>psql</>的<command>\?</>命令中可能崩溃(Meng Qingzhong)
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix one-byte buffer overrun in <application>libpq</>'s
      <function>PQprintTuples</> (Xi Wang)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
   修复<application>libpq</>的<function>PQprintTuples</>中一个字节缓冲区溢出(Xi Wang)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      This ancient function is not used anywhere by
      <productname>PostgreSQL</> itself, but it might still be used by some
      client code.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
    这个以往函数不会被<productname>PostgreSQL</>自身使用，但是它可能
通过客户端代码被使用。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Rearrange configure's tests for supplied functions so it is not
      fooled by bogus exports from libedit/libreadline (Christoph Berg)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
   为提供的函数重新分配配置测试，
   因此它不会通过libedit/libreadline虚假输出被愚弄(Christoph Berg)
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Ensure Windows build number increases over time (Magnus Hagander)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
    确保随时间推移Windows编译数增加(Magnus Hagander)
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Make <application>pgxs</> build executables with the right
      <literal>.exe</> suffix when cross-compiling for Windows
      (Zoltan Boszormenyi)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
   当Windows交叉编译时，使得<application>pgxs</>建立具有正确<literal>.exe</>后缀的可执行文件(Zoltan Boszormenyi)
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Add new timezone abbreviation <literal>FET</> (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
   添加新的时区缩写<literal>FET</> (Tom Lane)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      This is now used in some eastern-European time zones.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
    这被用于一些东欧时区。
</para>
    </listitem>

   </itemizedlist>

  </sect2>
 </sect1>

 <sect1 id="release-8-3-22">
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
  <title>Release 8.3.22</title>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
  <title>版本8.3.22</title>

  <formalpara>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
  <title>Release date:</title>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
  <title>发布日期：</title>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
  <para>2012-12-06</para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
  <para>2012-12-06</para>
  </formalpara>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
   This release contains a variety of fixes from 8.3.21.
   For information about new features in the 8.3 major release, see
   <xref linkend="release-8-3">.
  </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
    该发布包含来自8.3.21中各种修复。关于8.3主要发布中新特性信息，
参阅<xref linkend="release-8-3">。
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
   The <productname>PostgreSQL</> community will stop releasing updates
   for the 8.3.X release series in February 2013.
   Users are encouraged to update to a newer release branch soon.
  </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
   <productname>PostgreSQL</>社区在2013年2月为8.3.X发布系列停止发布更新。
   鼓励用户尽快更新到新版本分支。
</para>

  <sect2>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
  <title>Migration to Version 8.3.22</title>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
  <title>迁移到版本8.3.22</title>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
    A dump/restore is not required for those running 8.3.X.
   </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
   运行8.3.X不需要备份/恢复。
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
    However, if you are upgrading from a version earlier than 8.3.17,
    see <xref linkend="release-8-3-17">.
   </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
   然而，如果从8.3.17更早版本更新，参阅8.3.17发布说明。
</para>

  </sect2>

  <sect2>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
  <title>Changes</title>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
  <title>变化</title>
   <itemizedlist>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix multiple bugs associated with <command>CREATE INDEX
      CONCURRENTLY</> (Andres Freund, Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
    修复与<command>CREATE INDEX CONCURRENTLY</>相关的多个错误(Andres Freund, Tom Lane)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix <command>CREATE INDEX CONCURRENTLY</> to use
      in-place updates when changing the state of an index's
      <structname>pg_index</> row.  This prevents race conditions that could
      cause concurrent sessions to miss updating the target index, thus
      resulting in corrupt concurrently-created indexes.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
     当改变索引<structname>pg_index</>行状态的时候，修复<command>CREATE INDEX CONCURRENTLY</>以使用适当更新。
这可以防止竞争条件，它可以导致并发会话错过更新目标索引，从而造成损坏同时创建索引。
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Also, fix various other operations to ensure that they ignore
      invalid indexes resulting from a failed <command>CREATE INDEX
      CONCURRENTLY</> command.  The most important of these is
      <command>VACUUM</>, because an auto-vacuum could easily be launched
      on the table before corrective action can be taken to fix or remove
      the invalid index.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
     此外，修复其他各种操作以确保他们忽视由失败<command>CREATE INDEX CONCURRENTLY</>导致的无效索引。
最重要的是，这些是<command>VACUUM</>，因为
在该表上采取纠正措施以修复或者删除无效索引之前自动清理很容易被发动。

</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Avoid corruption of internal hash tables when out of memory
      (Hitoshi Harada)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
     当内存不足的时候，避免内部哈希表的损坏(Hitoshi Harada) 
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix planning of non-strict equivalence clauses above outer joins
      (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
    修复外部连接上非严格等价子句的规划(Tom Lane)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      The planner could derive incorrect constraints from a clause equating
      a non-strict construct to something else, for example
      <literal>WHERE COALESCE(foo, 0) = 0</>
      when <literal>foo</> is coming from the nullable side of an outer join.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
    规划器可以从子句等同于非严格结构中别的方面获取不正确限制，
比如<literal>WHERE COALESCE(foo, 0) = 0</>
当<literal>foo</>来自外部链接的空侧端时。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Improve planner's ability to prove exclusion constraints from
      equivalence classes (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
    完善规划器来自等价类排除约束能力(Tom Lane)
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix partial-row matching in hashed subplans to handle cross-type cases
      correctly (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
    修复散列子查询中部分行匹配以正确处理交叉类型情况(Tom Lane)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      This affects multicolumn <literal>NOT IN</> subplans, such as
      <literal>WHERE (a, b) NOT IN (SELECT x, y FROM ...)</>
      when for instance <literal>b</> and <literal>y</> are <type>int4</>
      and <type>int8</> respectively.  This mistake led to wrong answers
      or crashes depending on the specific datatypes involved.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
     这影响了多列<literal>NOT IN</>子计划，比如<literal>WHERE (a, b) NOT IN (SELECT x, y FROM ...)</>。
 当比如<literal>b</>和<literal>y</>分别为<type>int4</>和<type>int8</>的时候。
 这个错误导致了错误结果或者依赖于涉及到的特定数据类型的崩溃。
 
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Acquire buffer lock when re-fetching the old tuple for an
      <literal>AFTER ROW UPDATE/DELETE</> trigger (Andres Freund)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
   当为<literal>AFTER ROW UPDATE/DELETE</>触发器重新读取旧元组的时候，
   获取缓冲锁(Andres Freund)
   
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      In very unusual circumstances, this oversight could result in passing
      incorrect data to the precheck logic for a foreign-key enforcement
      trigger.  That could result in a crash, or in an incorrect decision
      about whether to fire the trigger.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
      在非常特殊的情况下，这种疏忽可能导致传递
不正确的数据来预检查外键执行触发器逻辑。
这可能会导致系统崩溃，或者关于是否触发触发器的一个不正确的决定。

</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix <command>REASSIGN OWNED</> to handle grants on tablespaces
      (&Aacute;lvaro Herrera)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
    修复<command>REASSIGN OWNED</>以处理在表空间上的授权(&Aacute;lvaro Herrera)
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Ignore incorrect <structname>pg_attribute</> entries for system
      columns for views (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
     为视图上系统列忽略不正确<structname>pg_attribute</>项(Tom Lane)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Views do not have any system columns.  However, we forgot to
      remove such entries when converting a table to a view.  That's fixed
      properly for 9.3 and later, but in previous branches we need to defend
      against existing mis-converted views.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
     视图没有任何系统列。但是，当转换表到视图时，我们忘了删除这些项。
这在9.3及更高版本中被正确修复，但在以往的分支中我们需要防御现有错误转换视图。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix rule printing to dump <literal>INSERT INTO <replaceable>table</>
      DEFAULT VALUES</literal> correctly (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
     修复规则输出以正确备份<literal>INSERT INTO <replaceable>table</> DEFAULT VALUES</literal>(Tom Lane)
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Guard against stack overflow when there are too many
      <literal>UNION</>/<literal>INTERSECT</>/<literal>EXCEPT</> clauses
      in a query (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
   当在查询中有许多<literal>UNION</>/<literal>INTERSECT</>/<literal>EXCEPT</>子句的时候，
   防止堆栈溢出(Tom Lane)
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Prevent platform-dependent failures when dividing the minimum possible
      integer value by -1 (Xi Wang, Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
    当最小可能整数值除以-1的时候，避免平台依赖错误(Xi Wang, Tom Lane)
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix possible access past end of string in date parsing
      (Hitoshi Harada)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
     修复日期解析中可能访问字符串结束端(Hitoshi Harada)
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Produce an understandable error message if the length of the path name
      for a Unix-domain socket exceeds the platform-specific limit
      (Tom Lane, Andrew Dunstan)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
    如果Unix域套接字路径名长度超过指定平台限制，那么产生可理解错误消息(Tom Lane, Andrew Dunstan)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Formerly, this would result in something quite unhelpful, such as
      <quote>Non-recoverable failure in name resolution</>.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
    之前，这可能导致一些无用的东西，比如<quote>域名解析中不可恢复故障</>。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix memory leaks when sending composite column values to the client
      (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
   当发送复合列值到客户端的时候，修复内存泄露(Tom Lane)
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Make <application>pg_ctl</> more robust about reading the
      <filename>postmaster.pid</> file (Heikki Linnakangas)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
   采取<application>pg_ctl</>使得读取<filename>postmaster.pid</>文件更加鲁棒性(Heikki Linnakangas)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix race conditions and possible file descriptor leakage.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
   修复竞争条件和可能文件描述符泄露。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix possible crash in <application>psql</> if incorrectly-encoded data
      is presented and the <varname>client_encoding</> setting is a
      client-only encoding, such as SJIS (Jiang Guiqing)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
    如果给定错误编码数据，并且<varname>client_encoding</>设置是客户端编码，比如SJIS，
修复<application>psql</>中可能崩溃(Jiang Guiqing)
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix bugs in the <filename>restore.sql</> script emitted by
      <application>pg_dump</> in <literal>tar</> output format (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
    修复在<literal>tar</>输出格式中通过<application>pg_dump</>发出的<filename>restore.sql</>脚本中错误(Tom Lane)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      The script would fail outright on tables whose names include
      upper-case characters.  Also, make the script capable of restoring
      data in <option>-&minus;inserts</> mode as well as the regular COPY mode.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
   该脚本可能在名字包含大小写字母的表中完全失败。
   同时，使得该脚本可以恢复<option>--inserts</>模式以及规则COPY模式中的数据。 
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix <application>pg_restore</> to accept POSIX-conformant
      <literal>tar</> files (Brian Weaver, Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
    修复<application>pg_restore</>以接受符合POSIX标准的<literal>tar</>文件(Brian Weaver, Tom Lane)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      The original coding of <application>pg_dump</>'s <literal>tar</>
      output mode produced files that are not fully conformant with the
      POSIX standard.  This has been corrected for version 9.3.  This
      patch updates previous branches so that they will accept both the
      incorrect and the corrected formats, in hopes of avoiding
      compatibility problems when 9.3 comes out.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
