  <title>发布日期：</title>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
  <para>2010-12-16</para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
  <para>2010-12-16</para>
  </formalpara>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
   This release contains a variety of fixes from 8.3.12.
   For information about new features in the 8.3 major release, see
   <xref linkend="release-8-3">.
  </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
     该发布包含来自8.3.12的各种修复。关于8.3主要发布的新特性信息，参阅
 <xref linkend="release-8-3">。
</para>

  <sect2>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
    <title>Migration to Version 8.3.13</title>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
    <title>迁移到版本8.3.13</title>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
    A dump/restore is not required for those running 8.3.X.
    However, if you are upgrading from a version earlier than 8.3.8,
    see <xref linkend="release-8-3-8">.
   </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
     运行8.3.X不需要备份/恢复。然而，如果从8.3.8更早版本更新，
 参阅8.3.8发布说明。
</para>

  </sect2>

  <sect2>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
  <title>Changes</title>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
  <title>变化</title>
   <itemizedlist>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Force the default
      <link linkend="guc-wal-sync-method"><varname>wal_sync_method</></link>
      to be <literal>fdatasync</> on Linux (Tom Lane, Marti Raudsepp)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
    强迫缺省<link linkend="guc-wal-sync-method"><varname>wal_sync_method</></link>
    为Linux上<literal>fdatasync</>(Tom Lane, Marti Raudsepp)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      The default on Linux has actually been <literal>fdatasync</> for many
      years, but recent kernel changes caused <productname>PostgreSQL</> to
      choose <literal>open_datasync</> instead.  This choice did not result
      in any performance improvement, and caused outright failures on
      certain filesystems, notably <literal>ext4</> with the
      <literal>data=journal</> mount option.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
     Linux上的缺省很多年一直<literal>fdatasync</>，
但最近的内核变化反而引起<productname>PostgreSQL</>到选择<literal>open_datasync</>。
这一选择不会引起任何性能改进，并且在某些文件系统造成彻底的失败，
尤其是带有<literal>data=journal</>安装选项的<literal>ext4</>。 

</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix assorted bugs in WAL replay logic for GIN indexes (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
    修复GIN索引WAL回放逻辑中各种错误(Tom Lane)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      This could result in <quote>bad buffer id: 0</> failures or
      corruption of index contents during replication.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
   这可能导致<quote>bad buffer id: 0</>错误或者复制过程中索引内容的损坏。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix recovery from base backup when the starting checkpoint WAL record
      is not in the same WAL segment as its redo point (Jeff Davis)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
    当开始检查点WAL记录不在同一WAL段作为重做点，修复基础备份恢复(Jeff Davis) 
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix persistent slowdown of autovacuum workers when multiple workers
      remain active for a long time (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
    当多个执行者长时间保持活跃，修复autovacuum持久延迟(Tom Lane)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      The effective <varname>vacuum_cost_limit</> for an autovacuum worker
      could drop to nearly zero if it processed enough tables, causing it
      to run extremely slowly.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
      为自动清理者的有效<varname>vacuum_cost_limit</>可能会删除到几乎为零，
 如果它处理了足够的表，导致它运行得非常慢。 
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Add support for detecting register-stack overrun on <literal>IA64</>
      (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
   添加支持检测<literal>IA64</>上寄存器堆栈溢出(Tom Lane)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      The <literal>IA64</> architecture has two hardware stacks.  Full
      prevention of stack-overrun failures requires checking both.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
    <literal>IA64</>结构有两个硬件堆栈。
全面预防堆栈溢出错误需要检查两者。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Add a check for stack overflow in <function>copyObject()</> (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
    添加<function>copyObject()</>中的堆栈溢出检查(Tom Lane)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Certain code paths could crash due to stack overflow given a
      sufficiently complex query.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
    某些代码路径可能崩溃，因堆栈溢出产生一个足够复杂的查询。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix detection of page splits in temporary GiST indexes (Heikki
      Linnakangas)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
   修复临时GiST索引中页面拆分检查(Heikki Linnakangas)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      It is possible to have a <quote>concurrent</> page split in a
      temporary index, if for example there is an open cursor scanning the
      index when an insertion is done.  GiST failed to detect this case and
      hence could deliver wrong results when execution of the cursor
      continued.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
      它可能在临时索引中有一个<quote>并发</>页拆分，
例如，当插入完成的时候，如果有一个打开的游标扫描索引，
当游标继续执行的时候，GiST未能检测这种情况，并因此可能提供错误的结果。

</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Avoid memory leakage while <command>ANALYZE</>'ing complex index
      expressions (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
    当<command>ANALYZE</>复杂索引表达式的时候，避免内存泄露(Tom Lane)
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Ensure an index that uses a whole-row Var still depends on its table
      (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
    确保使用整行Var的索引仍然依赖于它的表(Tom Lane) 
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      An index declared like <literal>create index i on t (foo(t.*))</>
      would not automatically get dropped when its table was dropped.
     </para>
